A man has appeared before magistrates charged with murder after a 24-year-old was stabbed to death on Christmas Day.

Joe Lewis, from Rustington, West Sussex, was knifed in the chest at a flat in Montague Street in the centre of Brighton at around 1am. 

Sussex Police say the victim – who is believed to have been visiting the flat – died at the scene. 

